inference:
The inequalities $|x-3|\leq y$ and $y\leq 4-|x-1|$ can be rewritten as $y\geq |x-3|$ and $y\leq 4-|x-1|$.  The graph of $y=|x-3|$ is a V-shaped graph with vertex at $(3,0)$, and the graph of $y=4-|x-1|$ is an upside-down V-shaped graph with vertex at $(1,4)$.  The region defined by these inequalities is the region between these two graphs, which is a parallelogram.

[asy]
unitsize(0.8inch);
real func (real x) {return(abs(x-3));}
real func2 (real x) {return(4-abs(x-1));}
draw(graph(func,-1,5),red);
draw(graph(func2,-1,5),blue);
draw((-1,0)--(5,0));
draw((0,-1)--(0,5));
dot("$y=|x-3|$",(5,func(5)),NE,red);
dot("$y=4-|x-1|$",(5,func2(5)),NE,blue);
fill((-1,0)--(1,3)--(3,1)--(5,0)--cycle,gray(0.7));
[/asy]

The base of the parallelogram has length $5 - (-1) = 6$, and the height is $4 - 0 = 4$.  Therefore, the area of the parallelogram is $6 \cdot 4 = \boxed{24}$.

